HEADWORD: Cack
<hw>Cack</hw> <pr>(k⟦acr⟧k)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>cakken</ets>, fr. L. <ets>cacare</ets>; akin to Gr.
<grk>kakka^n</grk>, and to OIr. <ets>cacc</ets> dung; cf. AS.
<ets>cac</ets>.]</ety> <def>To ease the body by stool; to go to
stool.</def> <rj><au>Pope.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

